.TH LPF-TABLE 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.0" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-table \- manage dynamic policy tables
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf table [\-\-json] <name> <add|delete|replace|flush|counters>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage dynamic policy tables without a full policy reload.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable table element and counter data
.TP
\-\-ttl <duration>
attach a time\-to\-live where supported
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf table threats add 203.0.113.10
lpf table threats counters \-\-json
lpf table threats replace threats.txt
lpf table threats flush
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Replacement must be atomic and reversible.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-plan(8), lpf\-rules(8)
